cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.PF 

This paper discusses the performance analysis of IEEE 802.11 Distributed Coordination Function (DCF) in wireless local area networks (WLANs) under high interference and capture effects. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also considers channel conditions and proposes a new mechanism to improve the performance of IEEE 802.11 DCF, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the impact of multipath fading, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses a multidimensional Markov chain model, which could be related to cs.PF (Performance).
